The '''Human Rights Organization of Judea and Samaria''' (also '''Yesha Human Rights Organization''' ({{lang-he|ארגון זכויות אדם ביש"ע}}) is an [[Israel]]i [[non-governmental organization]] (NGO) headed by [[Orit Strook]].

The organization was established in 1999. Its stated goals are to defend the [[human rights|human]] and [[civil rights]] of Jewish Israelis living in the [[West Bank]], and formerly in the [[Gaza Strip]]. The organization say that these citizens - commonly referred to as [[Israeli settlement|settlers]] - are not adequately defended by other human rights organizations it identifies as [[Left-wing politics|left-wing]], such as [[B'Tselem]]. The organization cooperates and uses the legal advice of the {{Interlanguage link multi|Legal Forum for the Land of Israel|he|3=פורום משפטי למען ארץ ישראל|vertical-align=sup}}.

One aspect of its activities is to report on alleged discrimination of settlers by the [[Israeli Police]].<ref>[http://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/128809 Statistics Show Police Discrimination Against Yesha Jews], ''[[Israel National News]]'', 11 December 2008.</ref>

